article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 52, Oral Roberts 49
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Solomon Bozeman scored 17 points, including 15 in the second half, to lead Arkansas-Little Rock over Oral Roberts 52-49 in the third round of the Las Vegas Holiday Hoops Classic on Wednesday night. Bozeman went 11 of 15 from the free throw line. Daylon Guy added 13 points and six rebounds for the Trojans (7-6), who trailed 28-21 at halftime and by nine early in the second. Damen Bell-Holter led Oral Roberts (4-8) with 16 points. Steve Roundtree had 11 points and 13 rebounds for the Golden Eagles, who were outrebounded 43-33. After Bozeman made one free throw with four seconds left, Warren Niles missed a potential tying 3-pointer just before the buzzer. Early in the second half, Arkansas-Little Rock went on a 11-2 run to tie it. The Trojans took the advantage for good at 43-42 with 6:41 left.
